mber Revolution of 1868 in which Queen Isabel II was deposed. European Sephardic Jews, galvanized by their perception of a tolerant Spain, decided to undertake a major project to initiate negotiations with the Spanish state.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aJewsxLegal status, laws, etc.zSpainxHistoryy19th century. 0aSephardimzSpainxHistoryy19th century. 0aSynagoguesxLaw and legislationzSpainxHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aEuropean History.  aHaim Guedalla.  aInquisition.  aJudaism.  aLa Gloriosa.  aProtestantism.  aSeptember Revolution.  aSpain.  acivil rights.  afreedom of religion.  aminorities.  apersecution.  asephardic Jews.  atolerance.1 aPeterson, Justin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068820708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishz978311070477808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020z9783110704570oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z97831106963010 cprintz978164469437440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644694381?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644694381423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781644694381/original  a978-3-11-068820-7  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Packag